      • turnAndMoveEncoders

        public void turnAndMoveEncoders(Vector leftVector,
                                Vector rightVector,
                                double encodersLeft,
                                double encodersRight)
        Turn and move at the same time for a certain amount of encoder ticks.
        Parameters:
        leftVector - The left motor vector.
        rightVector - The right motor vector.
        encodersLeft - The amount of encoders that the left side of the robot should travel.
        encodersRight - The amount of encoders that the right side of the robot should travel.
        Throws:
        InvalidMoveCommandException - Throws this exception if you tried to move the robot in an impossible way. (ex: 0 power, move 2000 encoder ticks).
        DumpsterFireException - Throws this exception if you try and move negative encoder distances. Change the power to change direction.
